            <title>Swedish manufacturer acquires U.S. grease maker</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	KANSAS CITY, MO--(Marketwire - April 4, 2011) - STRATCO, Inc. (online at: &lt;a href="http://ctt.marketwire.com/?release=740423&amp;amp;id=214687&amp;amp;type=1&amp;amp;url=http%3a%2f%2fwww.stratcoinc.com%2f"&gt;www.Stratcoinc.com&lt;/a&gt;), an industry leader in providing engineering design, equipment and R&amp;amp;D for the grease, petrochemical, asphalt, roofing and chemical industries, is excited to learn about the announcement by Sweden-based grease manufacturer, Axel Christiernsson -- one of STRATCO&amp;#39;s recent customers -- of their mid-March acquisition of US-based grease maker, Jesco Resources, STRATCO&amp;#39;s very first customer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;quot;We have had great experiences with both Axel and Jesco as valued customers over the years,&amp;quot; said Cecilia Mancero, Vice President of International Sales at STRATCO, Inc. &amp;quot;Now that these companies are merging, we are excited to enhance our ongoing relationship with them, and we envision a bright, long-lasting and mutually prosperous relationship between STRATCO and Axel/Jesco.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	For STRATCO, best known for its world famous STRATCO&amp;reg; Contactor&amp;trade; reactor -- the most efficient batch reactor employed in manufacturing lubricating grease -- the announcement of Axel&amp;#39;s purchase of Jesco is of particular significance. Jesco bought the very first STRATCO Contactor reactor (installed in 1929), a machine that the company is still operating today.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Jesco purchased its second STRATCO Contactor reactor in 2000. Axel has purchased STRATCO equipment for their plants in the Netherlands and in Sweden to allow for increased production needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The acquisition of Jesco significantly expands Axel&amp;#39;s global presence. Axel currently produces more than 20,000 metric tons of grease annually and has sites located in France, the Netherlands and in Sweden.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Axel and Jesco are longtime clients of STRATCO, and use STRATCO&amp;#39;s technology to grow and improve their products and operations. STRATCO looks forward to future opportunities to support Axel and Jesco in their continued growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;quot;Our technology -- focusing on the best equipment and the best process -- enables us to strive to achieve and deliver excellence,&amp;quot; Mancero said.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	To learn more about STRATCO, Inc. please visit: &lt;a href="http://www.Stratcoinc.com"&gt;www.Stratcoinc.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	STRATCO, Inc. was founded in 1928 and provides engineering design, equipment and R&amp;amp;D for the grease, petrochemical, asphalt, roofing and chemical industries. STRATCO process equipment is backed by 83 years of experience with a customer base in 60 countries on 6 continents. STRATCO, Inc. is a certified Woman-Owned Business by the Women&amp;#39;s Business Enterprise National Council.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/overall_equipment_effectiveness/~4/FYKAydk1I_0" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
